article.headline: Murray St. 88, Tennessee St. 74
article.story: MURRAY, Ky. -- Ivan Aska scored 17 points and Murray State defeated Tennessee State 88-74 in the first round of the Ohio Valley Conference Tournament on Tuesday night. Trailing 45-38 at halftime, Tennessee State (12-18) used a 10-2 run to take a 48-47 lead with 16:45 remaining. The Racers (19-11) responded with 10 straight points, and led by no fewer than four the rest of the way. Murray State used a 12-2 run to break an early tie and take a 24-12 lead on two Kevin Thomas free throws with 10:08 left in the first half. Top-seeded Murray State will face No. 4 seed Morehead State on Friday. The Racers had six players in double figures as Isacc Miles scored 15, Danero Thomas 14, Tony Easley and Kevin Thomas had 12 each and Jeffrey McClain notched 10 points. Robinson had 15 points for the Tigers, who beat Murray State in the conference semifinals last season.
